		<!-- message -->
		<div>Im tired of seeing the same old complaints on this thread, if you want to take a side, at least read the fucking thread, thank you. I already apologized for posting on the wrong section.<br />
<br />
I already said that we got wiped by the frenzy, and my problem isnt with Bubba and Burro stepping in to kill it. Its the disregard for commonly accepted raid rules. You get on the list. You work together with the other people in the zone who are trying to accomplish the same thing. We had been killing this mob for 30+ hours at this point, the raid size fluctuating as people came and left. We were in a low point for the number of people in the raid, and we wiped. We would have welcomed Bubba and Burro into the raid, had they asked. He's just selfish. Thats my point. He will take advantage when he's not technically breaking the rules but completely disregarding other players and the commonly accepted practices of public raiding. If he steals your shit on your next raid, I did the best I could to warn you.<br />
<br />
(as a side note, to those people who say we have no right to the mob because we didn't have the manpower to take it anyway... Bubba and Burro got wiped by the same mob... why does that give them a right to it? Perhaps we could have worked together to kill the mob, but no, that would be co-operation and we won't have any of that, will we?)<br />
<br />
If he's such a fucking hero, why didn't he apoligize for wiping us out? Why didnt he offer to rez us? Why did he kill the mob, ignore all our /tells and log as soon as it was dead? Because he knew what he was doing was wrong, and did it anyway. Also, he already said he did it, and doesnt care. Case closed. <br />
<br />
As for the &quot;smear campaign&quot;. I can only answer for my own actions. I spoke with the issue to Burro when he was online with /tells, until he asked me to stop sending him /tells. I havent talked to him since. I never advertised ANYTHING in PoK or Bazaar or any zone ever. I only posted here, and what I posted were just facts. Other people that were present in the raid have been spamming public zones with warnings about them, and I've seen them. I don't condone their actions, thats why I didn't state my concerns the same way. I feel that's what the boards are for, not PoK, so I posted here instead.<br />
<br />
<br />
So heres my agrument to Burro. Burro asks &quot;Show me one person that has proof that I have stolen, lied, or done anything else that would render me dishonest or untrustworthy. I've been playing this game for 5 years, so there must be someone to back up your claims if they are true.&quot;<br />
<br />
Yes there is Burro, and in fact, the person I have to back me up is YOU.<br />
Regard:<br />
<br />
&quot;98% of the time I spend on this game is spent being the nice guy, and in my occasional moments of boredom I have managed to do some stuff that I wouldn't normally do&quot;<br />
<br />
&quot; ... I did indeed kill the Fabled Frenzied Ghoul. &quot;<br />
<br />
&quot;Wah. Can't say I felt like a twat, I did feel like killing stuff though.&quot;<br />
<br />
So you felt like being a jerk in lower guk? Your second personality came out to kill the ghoul, and you aren't accountable? Its that other 2% of the time that you have to be accountable for, Burro. You can't just be an awesome nice guy 98% of the time, and a prick 2% of the time, and hope people forgive you because &quot;he's usually so nice&quot;. Had you been in a better mood, you might have gave those dead players in GuK a rez. But that day, you felt like being a dick and killed the frenzy and logged. Sorry, &quot;I felt like being a jerk that day&quot; doesn't work for me. <br />
<br />
I'm tired of addressing the same old flames and shit that pops up on this board. At least come up with something that hasn't already been addressed.<br />
<br />
